content.description: make your way straight up the vertical tiger stripes using small holds and side pulls. there is a couple fun moves towards the top i guess you could call the crux.
content.protection: set up a top rop on the fence above. youl get some rop drag so dont use your best rope
content.location: route is at the south end of the beach up the veritacal tiger strips

content.description: Route can be started on either side. Use the hand holds on the stripes to traverse across. Stay low to the ground, avoid going above the large foot hold in the center of the route. This is a great route for beginners or to warm up on!
content.protection: Since this route is low to the ground and on a beach, no protection is needed but a pad is still nice to land on.
content.location: This route is in the middle of Grime Dog Wall on either side of the center of the tiger stripes. Look for chalked hand holds and check out the pictures for more info.

content.description: pretty mellow route in the middle of the wall slightly to the north of the middle maby. Cruiser route.. names just for fun
content.protection: top rope with a lil rope drag
content.location: a little north of the middle of the grime dog wall

content.description: This problem goes straight up the far right end of the bouldering wall on thinner but good holds and tops out on some sidepulls. Certainly spicier to top out than the problem up the center of the wall.
content.location: Far right end of the wall where Love All is painted on the bouldering wall.

content.description: Route can be started on either side. Use the hand holds on the stripes to traverse across. Go up and over the center peak and back down to the other side. This is a great route for beginners or to warm up on!
content.protection: Low to the ground on a beach, so no protection needed, but a pad is good to have when going higher up.
content.location: This route is in the middle of Grime Dog Wall on either side of the center of the tiger stripes. Look for chalked hand holds and check out the pictures for more info.

content.description:
the route pictured is prolly the easiest spot to top out. its a lil sandy up there so you mite want to bring a broom to sweep the jug finish at the top. Its a lil heady just because its flaky cement.

also fun for traverses and there are some other spots to top out that mite be a little harder/scetchier..
content.protection: sand is soft. i jumped from near the top with no shoes on and was fine.
content.location: drive north on ocean blvd and there is a staircase at the end of the road. at the bottom of the staircase you will see the wall just south.
